onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Ad Quint. Frat.</I> 1.1.21</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note4" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">4</A>
Q. Cicero was really <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">propraetor</SPAN>; see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#note48
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
note on <I>Jul.</I> liv.1</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note5" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref5
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">5</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Imagines</SPAN> were waxen masks of ancestors of noble (<I>i.e.</I>, senatorial) rank, kept in the hall (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">atrium</SPAN>) of their descendants.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note6" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">6</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#20.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Jul.</I> xx.3, note</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note7" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref7
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">7</A>
According to the <I>Thes. Ling. Lat.</I> <I>s.v.</I> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">collybus</SPAN>, Suetonius


<A ID="p127x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p127)</SPAN>misunderstood Cassius, who used <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">collybus</SPAN> of a kind of cake. In general, see Scott, <I>Mem. Amer. Acad. in Rome</I>, xi.12 f.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note8" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">8</A>
<I>i.e.</I> Hadrian.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note9" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">9</A>
<I>Annales</I>, 502, Vahlen<SPAN CLASS="superscript">2</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note10" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref10
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">10</A>
Since the time of Sulla only senators were eligible for the position of tribune.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note11" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref11
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">11</A>
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/fam11.shtml#20
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Cic. <I>Epist. ad Fam.</I> 11.20.1</A>; according to
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2C*.html#62.6
	"TARGET="Velleius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Vell. Paterc. 2.62.6</A>, Cicero punned on the double meaning of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">tollo</SPAN>, "raise" and "put out of the way."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note12" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref12
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>
A game still common in Italy, in which the contestants thrust out their fingers (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">micare digitis</SPAN>), the one naming correctly the number thrust out by his opponent being the winner.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note13" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref13
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">13</A>
The term applied to a victorious general by his soldiers.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note14" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref14
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">14</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#note36
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
note on <I>Jul.</I> xxxix.2</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note15" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref15
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">15</A>
The sacred precinct at Alexandria (<SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">τὸ καλούμενον Σῆμα, ὅ περίβολος ἧν</SPAN>,
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/17A1*.html#1.8.7
	"TARGET="Strabo_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Strabo,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Strabo, 17.1.8</A>) containing the tombs of Alexander and of the kings.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: And for further much more comprehensive details, be sure to follow the note there.
	</P></DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note16" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref16
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">16</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">nomenclator</SPAN> (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">nomenculator</SPAN>) was a slave whose duty it was to remind his master, or mistress, of the names of persons.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note17" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref17
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">17</A>
Applied to expeditions commanded by others, since as <SPAN CLASS="whole">commander-in‑chief</SPAN> he took the auspices before the army set out.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note18" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">18</A>
Crassus lost his standards at the battle of Carrhae in 53, and Antony through the defeat of his lieutenants in 40 and 36 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note19" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref19
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">19</A>
In the reign of Numa, and in 235 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, after the first Punic war.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note20" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">20</A>
The ovation was a lesser triumph, in which the general entered the city on foot, instead of in a chariot drawn by four horses (whence the term <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">triumphus curulis</SPAN>), and with other differences<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox('Loeb has '+BadF+'difference'+CloseF+'',WIDTH,100)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A> described by
	<A HREF="
