E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref25
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">25</A>
That is, he kept them apart from the rest in the companies in which they were first enrolled.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note26" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref26
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">26</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">phalerae</SPAN> were discs or plates of metal attached to a belt or to the harness of horses.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note27" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">27</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Se praecipitaverit</SPAN> means "hurled himself headlong," perhaps into the Tiber; more probably from some high place such as the Tarpeian Rock, or the roof of a building.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note28" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref28
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">28</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#101.4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. ci</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
