E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">29</A>
Suetonius is brief to the point of obscurity. The idea seems to be that the intentions of Augustus in establishing the principate, and the effect of the new régime on the public welfare, were equally good.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
