Dio 37.24</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note33" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref33
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">33</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Exigere</SPAN> is the technical term for making weights and measures correspond with the standards in charge of the aediles; see <SPAN CLASS="small">CIL</SPAN> <SPAN CLASS="smaller">XIV</SPAN>.4124<!--</A>CIL14-->.1, 2; <SPAN CLASS="small">X</SPAN>.8067.2; etc.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note34" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref34
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">34</A>
According to Richter, <I>Topographie von Rom</I>, p229, the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">regia</SPAN> was the main door, leading from the stage of the theatre to the colonnade.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
For Prof. Rolfe's detailed argument and a few other possibilities, see his
		<A HREF="
E/Journals/TAPA/45/Notes_on_Suetonius*.html#1
		"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Notes on Suetonius (TAPA 45:35‑38)</A>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note35" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref35
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">35</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">ergastula</SPAN> were prisons for slaves, who were made to work in chains in the fields.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Ergastulum.html
		"TARGET="princeps"
