<SPAN CLASS="smallcaps">Ergastulum</SPAN>
		</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note36" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref36
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">36</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Collegia</SPAN>, or guilds, of workmen were allowed and were numerous; not infrequently they were a pretext for some illegal secret organization.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Collegium.html
		"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Smith1,WIDTH,SmithWidth1)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="smallcaps">Collegium</SPAN>
		</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note37" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref37
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">37</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Sordibus</SPAN> refers especially to the mourning garb in which it was usual for the accused to appear in public.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note38" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref38
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">38</A>
That is, if he failed to win his suit, he should suffer the penalty that would have been inflicted on the defendant, if he had been convicted.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note39" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref39
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">39</A>
Men whose property amounted to 200,000 sesterces, or half of a knight's estate.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: Normally, yes; but the Loeb editor went too fast: see the article
		<A CLASS="smallcaps" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Ducenarii.html#2
		"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Smith1,WIDTH,SmithWidth1)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Ducenarii (2)
		</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note40" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref40
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">40</A>
Parricides were sewn up in a sack with a dog, a cock, a snake, and a monkey, and thrown into the sea or a river. The word is here used in its modern sense; <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#note41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">note on <I>Jul.</I> xlii.3</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note41" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">41</A>
These consisted of various immunities, especially those connected with the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">ius trium liberorum</SPAN> (see
Introd. p. x<!--</A>-->).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note42" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref42
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">42</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Orcivi</SPAN> or <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Orcini</SPAN>, "freedmen by the grace of Orcus," were slaves set free by their master's will. The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Orcivi senatores</SPAN> were those admitted by Mark Antony under pretence that they had been named in the papers left by Caesar.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note43" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref43
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">43</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Jul.</I> xx.1</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note44" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref44
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">44</A>
A very ancient tribunal, consisting at first of 105 members, three from each tribe, but later of 180. It sat in the Basilica Julia, with a spear (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">hasta</SPAN>), the ancient symbol of Quiritary <SPAN CLASS="whole">owner</SPAN>&shy;ship, planted before it. It was divided into four chambers, which usually sat separately, but sometimes altogether<!-- sic -->, or in two divisions.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Centumviri.html
		"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Smith1,WIDTH,SmithWidth1)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="smallcaps">Centumviri</SPAN>
		</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note45" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref45
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">45</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">decemviri stlitibus iudicandis</SPAN>.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Decemviri.html#Litibus_Judicandis
		"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Smith1,WIDTH,SmithWidth1)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="smallcaps">Decemviri</SPAN>
		</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note46" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref46
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">46</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#note20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
note on chap. xxii</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note47" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref47
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">47</A>
That is, were so old or infirm that they could not ride, or would cut a sorry figure if they did.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note48" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref48
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">48</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#note10
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
note on chap. x.2</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note49" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref49
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">49</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#note36
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
note on <I>Jul.</I> xxxix.2</A>, and <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#14
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chap. xiv</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note50" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref50
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">50</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Jul.</I> xli</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note51" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref51
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">51</A>
Augustus was a member of the latter because of his connection with the Octavian family; of the former, through his adoption into the Julian <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">gens</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note52" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref52
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">52</A>
That is, even by <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">iusta libertas</SPAN>, which conferred <SPAN CLASS="whole">citizen</SPAN>&shy;ship. Slaves who had been punished for crimes (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">facinora</SPAN>)


<A ID="p187x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p187)</SPAN>or disgraceful acts (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">flagitia</SPAN>) became on manumission <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">dediticii</SPAN>, "prisoners of war."

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
