E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref99
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">99</A>
With reference to the study of Archimedes, or perhaps to the general use of such elevated rooms in Syracuse.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note100" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref100
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">100</A>
"Little workshop"; a diminutive from <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">τέχνη</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note101" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref101
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">101</A>
Opposed to <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vestis forensis</SPAN> or <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">forensia</SPAN> (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vestimenta</SPAN>); <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Vitellius*.html#8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><I>Vit.</I> viii.1</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note102" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref102
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">102</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">cena recta</SPAN> was a regular dinner, at which the guests reclined on couches at a table, contrasted with <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">sportula</SPAN>, an informal meal
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Claudius*.html#21.4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<I>Claud.</I> xxi.4)
	</A>
or a distribution of food. See Friedländer, <I>Roman Life and Manners</I> (Eng. trans.), IV. pp77 ff.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note103" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref103
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">103</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#72
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. lxxii.2</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note104" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#ref104
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">104</A>
Tellers of marvellous tales; <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
https://www.curculio.org/Juvenal/s15.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Juvenal\'s 15th Satire'+Lat2+LatSearch+'aretalogus</SPAN>')"
onMouseOut="nd();">Juv. 15.16</A>, and Mayor <I>ad loc.</I> Doubtless the same as the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">fabulatores</SPAN>,
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#78.2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
lxxviii.2</A>, below.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: the Greek word means "people who discourse on virtue". See the interesting entry
		<A HREF="
